BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eeUZ7rJyWLMBqrGWnpvgZ
SUMMARY:Make a difference for cats and dogs in need!
DTSTAMP:20260413T005355Z
DTSTART:20260413T070000Z
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in using your time\, talent\, and energy to 
	support the vision of a healthy and happy home for every cat and dog in Wa
	shington?\n\nIf yes\, then please consider joining our Board!\n\nPawsitive
	 Alliance\, a volunteer driven tax-exempt nonprofit organization\, is havi
	ng an open call for Board Members. Founded in 2005\, the mission of Pawsit
	ive Alliance is to help end the euthanasia of adoptable dogs and cats in W
	ashington by increasing adoptions\, supporting spay and neuter programs\, 
	and improving pet retention.\n\nPawsitive Alliance advances are mission th
	rough our three programs:\n\n-  Adoption program: \\#WhyNotMePets campaign
	\, highlighting long-term homeless pets\, and supporting adoption events t
	o help homeless finds homes\n\n-  Spay/Neuter: providing vouchers and fina
	ncial and logistical support to increase surgeries and access to end pet o
	verpopulation and suffering\n\n-  Pet retention: collecting and distributi
	ng pet food and supplies and offering pet ID tags and microchips to keep p
	ets thriving with their caretakers\n\nOur programs and activities prioriti
	ze increasing services for pets\, people\, and places across Washington st
	ate with few resources.\n\nPawsitive Alliance’s biggest strengths are mark
	eting\, organizing\, fundraising\, and collaborating.  We work with more t
	han 50 human and animal-welfare partners each year. Since 2005\, we have h
	elped over 8\,000 animals find homes\, delivered over 170\,000 pounds of d
	onated pet food\, and facilitated more than 11\,000 spay and neuter surger
	ies.\n\nThe Pawsitive Alliance Board is a hands-on group of committed indi
	viduals\, investing their time and resources to support our mission.  As w
	e celebrate our 20th anniversary in 2025\, and look to the future\, we are
	 looking to add individuals from diverse backgrounds to join the Board and
	 help the organization’s continued success and growth.  Ideal candidates a
	re committed to our mission\, can commit at least 10-15 per month to the o
	rganization\, are able to represent the organization in the community\, ar
	e ready to engage in strategy setting\, fundraising and networking\, and b
	ring a well-rounded set of skills to a unique and hard-working team.​\n\nP
	awsitive Alliance is always interested in bringing greater diversity and n
	ew areas of expertise\, energy\, and skills to the Board. For more informa
	tion on the organization\, refer to our website at www.pawsitivealliance.o
	rg.  Please fill out our Board Application if you share our passion for he
	lping to end pet homelessness in Washington and are interested in serving 
	and helping end pet overpopulation.\n\nThose interested in applying should
	 email our Board Recruitment Committee at info@pawsitivealliance.org.\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cats-an
	d-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-04-13T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cat
	s-and-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-04-13T00
LOCATION:Pawsitive Alliance\, 14150 NE 20th St. F1-233\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_pEFeBd3WYzdiM55zzaF7
SUMMARY:Coworking Open House Week @ The Cloud Room
DTSTAMP:20260413T005355Z
DTSTART:20260413T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Curious about coworking and looking for the perfect spot to get
	 work done and reach your goals? Join us for a complimentary day during ou
	r upcoming Open House Week and experience what it’s like to be a part of o
	ur incredible community!\n\nWhat's Included:\n\nOne Free Trial Day: Pick a
	ny day during Open House Week to try out our coworking space\, free of cha
	rge! Arrive anytime 9am or later — whatever works best with your schedule.
	\n\nAccess to our beautiful workspace including quiet desk space with moni
	tors\, large lounge area\, phone booths\, bar\, and outdoor patio.\n\nComp
	limentary coffee\, tea\, snacks and kombucha.\n\nHigh-speed Wi-Fi\, printi
	ng\, and meeting rooms available for rent\n\nThe chance to meet like-minde
	d professionals and get a feel for the Cloud Room vibe.\n\nSpecial Offer:\
	n\nIf you love your free day with us and decide to become a member\, we’ll
	 waive your initiation fees when you sign up! How to Join:\n\nReserve your
	 free trial day by selecting one day of your choice on our Calendly \\(one
	 free trial day per person\\)\n\nShow up and enjoy your day at Cloud Room!
	 Be sure to check in with the staff at the front of the lounge so we can g
	ive you a quick tour of the space and get you set up with the wifi.\n\nSig
	n up for membership to take advantage of waived initiation fees.\n\nDon’t 
	miss this chance to test out our space\, meet amazing people\, and see if 
	Cloud Room is the perfect fit for your work needs!\n\nCurrent Promotions:\
	n\n⭐️ Sign up for a grounded membership and get your first month free \\+ 1
	0% off you first year of membership. 3 month commitment required.\n\n⭐️ Flo
	ating Membership Promo: Take 50% off your first full month of floating mem
	bership.\n\nSpaces are limited—RSVP today.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com
	/events/#/details/coworking-open-house-week-the-cloud-room/18423258/2026-0
	4-13T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/coworking-open-house-week
	-the-cloud-room/18423258/2026-04-13T00
LOCATION:The Cloud Room\, 1424 11th Ave Suite 400\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:q2ZX0i7iYOKVZoI4HMzVU
SUMMARY:TADAIMA: I'm Home
DTSTAMP:20260413T005355Z
DTSTART:20260413T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:After more than 80 years\, a treasured collection returns “home
	” to Seattle’s Japanese American community. In 1942 dozens of traditional 
	Boys’ and Girls’ Day dolls were entrusted to Bailey Gatzert Elementary Sch
	ool by Japanese American families facing forced incarceration. Most were n
	ever reclaimed after the war. Artist Miya Sukune uses recent research in M
	OHAI’s collection\, as well as interviews with Japanese American survivors
	 and their descendants\, to create an installation called “Tadaima\,” mean
	ing “I’m home.”\n\nTADAIMA: “I’m Home!” Bringing Seattle’s Girls’ and Boys
	’ Day Dolls Home reconnects the dolls with their traditional role of prote
	cting and blessing children. It invites visitors to celebrate the resilien
	ce\, memory\, and enduring traditions of the Japanese American Community.\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-04-13T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-04-13T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
