DESCRIPTION:Learn more about the birds at the Bellevue Botanical Garden. Jo
	in Eastside Audubon for a monthly walk that explores the birds and their h
	abitat in the Garden. This one-mile walk will be on trails with various su
	rfaces and may include gravel\, mulch\, or pavement. Please dress for the 
	weather and wear comfortable walking shoes. Parking in the lot is free. Fr
	om the parking lot enter the garden through the breezeway and turn left. M
	eet your guide in the covered Gathering Place. This walk is for any level 
	of birder and no experience is necessary. Bring binoculars if you have the
	m. There will be some available to loan for the walk. Each walk is $5 per 
	person. Registration is required.  \n\nSorry\, the June walk is full. View
	 our calendar to register for upcoming walks.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/audubon-bird-walk/15998889/2026-04-16T00\n\nFrom SEAt
