BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lbtQUzc_mTFa0u-n6ZTCr
SUMMARY:New Labor Organizer Training
DTSTAMP:20260413T005356Z
DTSTART:20260509T143000Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP HERE \\nHave you ever… \\n\\nWanted more rights at work?\\
	nWanted to fight back against the corporate class?\\nBeen thinking “I need
	 a union\\\,” but don’t know how to make it happen?\\n\\nThis workshop wil
	l teach you what you need to get started at your workplace! \\nThis is int
	ended for people at currently non-union workplaces who want to take the fi
	rst steps toward organizing\\\, whether you want to join an existing union
	\\\, form a new one\\\, or organizing demands of your boss without a union
	 at all. \\nOur experienced labor organizers will teach you how to have an
	 organizing conversation and how to form your Organizing Committee. \\nWhe
	n we organize\\\, we win! \\n\\nPLEASE NOTE: The Cathy Hillenbrand Communi
	ty Room is NOT at Cal Anderson! Do not believe Google Maps!\\nIt is at the
	 corner of 10th Ave E & John St.\\nThere will be a social to follow this e
	vent at Outer Planet Brewing!\n\nhttps://seattledsa.org/event/new-labor-or
	ganizer-training/\n\nFrom Seattle DSA
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/new-labor-organizer-training/
LOCATION:Cathy Hillenbrand Community Room\\\, 923 E John St\\\, Seattle\\\,
	 WA\\\, 98102\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seattle-dsa
CATEGORIES:Seattle DSA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_VWo9jbZQqmK7yFgnBRfZ
SUMMARY:Build a Better Union panel discussion
DTSTAMP:20260413T005356Z
DTSTART:20260509T143000Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP HERE \\nIn some unions\\\, it’s tough to get involved beyo
	nd paying dues. Maybe leadership is an exclusive club or maybe they’re jus
	t checked out\\\, but something needs to change. Even when you can get inv
	olved\\\, is it a struggle? Are you really being listened to? Are your cow
	orkers engaged with the union\\\, or just paper members? \\nBuilding democ
	ratic participation makes a stronger\\\, fighting union. Come hear from un
	ion members who are currently organizing to do just that\\\, even when uni
	on leadership doesn’t agree with them. Learn how these members are working
	 to build a better union from the inside\\\, and how you can apply their l
	essions to your own local. \\nIf you are a current union staffer\\\, we as
	k that you not attend this event. Please join us afterwards at Outer Plane
	t! \\nThe Cathy Hillenbrand Community Room is NOT at Cal Anderson! Do not 
	believe Google Maps!\\nIt is at the corner of 10th Ave E & John St. \\n\\n
	There will be a social to follow this event at Outer Planet Brewing!\n\nht
	tps://seattledsa.org/event/build-a-better-union-panel-discussion/\n\nFrom 
	Seattle DSA
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/build-a-better-union-panel-discussion/
LOCATION:Capitol Hill Branch Library\\\, 425 Harvard Ave E\\\, Seattle\\\, 
	WA\\\, 98102\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seattle-dsa
CATEGORIES:Seattle DSA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:yeTO2nOxVFxV1NsrTojvV
SUMMARY:May Labor Social
DTSTAMP:20260413T005356Z
DTSTART:20260509T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:RSVP HERE \\nParticipants in our two workshops today are invite
	d to continue their discussion and share what they learned at this social 
	just down the street at Outer Planet Brewing. Anyone is welcome whether yo
	u’re not a union member (yet)\\\, a long time union activist\\\, or anywhe
	re in between. \\nWe’ll also have members of our Unionize for Trans Rights
	 campaign at the social to discuss their work! \\nYou can register for the
	 Build A Better Union panel (for current union members) or the New Organiz
	er Training (for future union members)\\\, both immediately before this so
	cial!\n\nhttps://seattledsa.org/event/may-labor-social/\n\nFrom Seattle DS
	A
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/may-labor-social/
LOCATION:Outer Planet Brewing\\\, 1812 12th Avenue\\\, Seattle\\\, 98122\\\
	, United States
